Governor Abubakar Atiku Bagudu of Kebbi state has rejoiced with Christians on the celebration of Christmas, urging them to preach peace and unity among their followers and the citizenry. A press release signed by the Chief Press Secretary to the governor, Alhaji Abubakar Muazu Dakingari and made available to LEADERSHIP says Senator Abubakar Atiku Bagudu advised adherents to imbibe the virtues of love and compassion as exemplified by Christ, the Messiah. He affirmed commitment of his administration in supporting all religious groups within an atmosphere of freedom and liberty to worship and conduct their religious activities. Similarly, the Governor extended his New Year message to all people of the state and Nigerians with an appeal to intensifying prayers for peace and prosperity of the nation.